attributes.background:
The aims of the Carers Poverty Charter are:-

• To protect carers from  falling into poverty or financial hardship; 
• To reflect carers' different circumstances; 
• To help carers to combine caring with paid work and study; 
• To make the Carers’ Allowance easy to understand and straightforward to claim.

According to Ruth Marks, the Commissioner for Older People in Wales, each carer saves the UK economy an average of £15,000 per year. It is therefore indefensible for the UK Government to procrastinate in increasing the weekly Carers Allowance to a more realistic amount. Even £150 per week Carers' Allowance would not be enough - though it would be a start!
